  "title": "AutoComplete vs InstantSearch Result Count",
  "body": "Afternoon,\r\n\r\nQuestion I have on search result discrepancies between AutoComplete and InstantSearch. We're seeing a different count of results based on which tool is used.\r\n\r\nThe difference appears to be related to `&is_v=1` in the URL. I have read that this is for versioning, but I am seeing different results when this is present versus not.\r\n\r\nFor instance, a search using AutoComplete returns 14 results. The same search performed with InstantSearch (when that parameter is present) is 9. When I remove that parameter from the URL but perform the same search from InstantSearch I get 14 results.\r\n\r\nIs there a way to normalize these results?\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nBrian",
